                            <comment id="17779223" author="emilles" created="Tue, 24 Oct 2023 20:11:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This has to do with the order the elements are processed.  In Groovy 4, the header incl. class annotations is processed before the members like fields.  I have made changes to defer annotation processing until the class members have been resolved so you can make constant references like this.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/groovy/blob/77f525dd256f4ba033fc1ebe997922812cb8b7fa/src/main/java/org/codehaus/groovy/control/ResolveVisitor.java#L1327&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/groovy/blob/77f525dd256f4ba033fc1ebe997922812cb8b7fa/src/main/java/org/codehaus/groovy/control/ResolveVisitor.java#L1327&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
